Model

Conditions

Conditions Values
N_sample 100, 300, 500
N_Items 10, 50
r^2 of Cov on LV 0.1, 0.5
  • Pirors
    • BE_D: Diffuse prior for all parameters (Uniform)
    • BE_MI: Informative prior for only measurement params (Normal, LogN)
    • BE_I: Informative prior for all params
    • BE_M: Matched Informative prior for all params
  • 100 replications per condition

Data generation check

R^2 == 0.1

library(lavaan)
library(broom)
# generate data ------------------------------------------
sdat <- makeDat(
  N       = 10000,
  R2Y     = 0.2,
  R2eta   = 0.1,
  omega   = 0.2,
  tau0    = 0.4,
  tau1    = -0.2,
  linear  = T,
  ydist   = 'n',
  lambda  = 0.5,
  nsec    = 10,
  nfac    = 1,
  lvmodel = '2pl'
)

X <- sdat$x
theta <- sdat$theta
Y <- sdat$stan_dt$Y
Z <- sdat$stan_dt$Z

datax <- data.frame(X1 = X[,1], X2 = X[,2], Z, theta, Ztheta = Z*theta, Y)
round(colMeans(datax), 3); round(cov(datax), 3)

Non-convergence

  • nConv : Converged replications
  • nWarn : replications with warnings (for Bayes, the replications with 1.1 < Rhat < 1.2)
  • nError : Errors, non-convergence (no output at all in mplus; for Bayes, the replications with Rhat > 1.2)

Bias

  • Each dot indicates errors (estimate - true) of each replication.
  • Item slopes and intercepts are averaged
  • SE: Standard Errors for ML / Standard deviations for Bayes
  • Red dot indicates the bias (the mean of errors)
  • All non-converged replications are excluded (For Bayes, the replications with Rhat < 1.2 are used (not 1.1))

MSE Ratio

  • MSE ratio = MSE of ML / MSE of Bayesian
  • When MSE ratio = 1, no difference in MSE
